The United States is closely monitoring the situation in Ukraine and advocates for a de-escalation of violence, constitutional change, a coalition government, and early elections. They believe that the people of Ukraine should determine their own future. The US welcomes the release of former Prime Minister Yulia Tymoshenko and wishes her a speedy recovery. They urge an end to violence and a focus on peaceful dialogue, in accordance with Ukraine's constitution. The US will work with allies, Russia, and international organizations to support a strong, prosperous, unified, and democratic Ukraine. They value their relationship with Ukraine and will support them in their pursuit of democracy and economic development.